Weather App using OpenWeatherMap API (CLI)
Description:
This Python app allows users to fetch real-time weather data for any city using the OpenWeatherMap API. It displays temperature, humidity, weather description, and wind speed based on the city name input.
How It Works:
The user enters a city name.
The app sends a request to the OpenWeatherMap API with that city.
It parses the returned JSON data to extract:
Temperature (°C)
Weather description (e.g., "clear sky")
Humidity
Wind speed
Displays this information in the terminal.
